Note:
ORDERED SET - Insertion-Order Preserving HashSet Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements an OrderedSet, structurally an OrderedMap where
the value is always ignored. We keep the implementation distinct rather
than wrapping OrderedMap because the value slot would waste 8 bytes
per entry and the API names should reflect set semantics.

Entry structure (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  hash chain next (8 bytes)
  offset 16: order prev (8 bytes)
  offset 24: order next (8 bytes)

Header (48 bytes):
  offset 0:  buckets pointer
  offset 8:  capacity
  offset 16: count
  offset 24: order_head
  offset 32: order_tail
  offset 40: seed
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Let OSET_ENTRY_SIZE be 32
Let OSET_HEADER_SIZE be 48
Let OSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY be 16

@Reasoning
Hash an integer value using splitmix64 mix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same routine as OrderedMap.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-cryptographic.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_hash" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    Let h be v
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 18397679294719823053
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 14181476777654086739
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    If h is less than 0:
        Set h to 0 minus h
    End If
    Return h
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate an entry.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
32-byte alloc; set value, zero other fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_entry_create" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let e be proc allocate from Layout with OSET_ENTRY_SIZE
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 24, 0
    Return e
End Process

@Reasoning
Create empty ordered set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate header + bucket array (zero-init).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_create" returns Integer:
    Let os be proc allocate from Layout with OSET_HEADER_SIZE
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bytes be OSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY multiplied by 8
    Let buckets be proc allocate from Layout with bytes
    If buckets is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with os
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with buckets, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 0, buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 8, OSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 40, 2654435761
    Return os
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy ordered set, walking the order list and freeing entries.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate from order_head freeing each entry; then free buckets + header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_destroy" takes os as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 24
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let nx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 24
        proc deallocate from Layout with cur
        Set cur to nx
    End While
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 0
    If buckets is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with buckets
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with os
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Find entry by value via bucket-chain walk.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Hash, mask, walk chain comparing value field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_find" takes os as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc oset_hash with value
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If v is equal to value:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Resize: double capacity and rebucket. Order list is unchanged.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate new bucket array, walk order list, re-prepend each entry.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n + capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_resize" takes os as Integer returns Integer:
    Let old_buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 0
    Let old_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 8
    Let new_capacity be old_capacity multiplied by 2
    Let new_bytes be new_capacity multiplied by 8
    Let new_buckets be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
    If new_buckets is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than new_bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with new_buckets, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    Let new_mask be new_capacity minus 1
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 24
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let order_next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 24
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        Let h be proc oset_hash with v
        Let new_idx be h bitwise and new_mask
        Let head_addr be new_buckets plus (new_idx multiplied by 8)
        Let existing be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 8, existing
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, cur
        Set cur to order_next
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with old_buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 0, new_buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 8, new_capacity
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Add value (no-op if already present).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Resize if load >= 75%.
2) Find existing; if present, return 1.
3) Allocate entry, link into bucket chain and order tail, increment count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_add" takes os as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 16
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 8
    Let threshold be (capacity multiplied by 75) divided by 100
    If count is greater than or equal to threshold:
        Let r be proc oset_resize with os
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let existing be proc oset_find with os, value
    If existing is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let entry be proc oset_entry_create with value
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 0
    Let new_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 8
    Let mask be new_capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc oset_hash with value
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let existing_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 8, existing_head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, entry
    Let old_tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 32
    If old_tail is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 24, entry
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with old_tail, 24, entry
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 16, old_tail
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 32, entry
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 16, count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if find returns non-zero.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_contains" takes os as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e be proc oset_find with os, value
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Remove value, unlinking from both bucket chain and order list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk bucket chain finding the matching entry, splice it out of both
the chain and the order list, then free.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_remove" takes os as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc oset_hash with value
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let prev be 0
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If cv is equal to value:
            Let next_chain be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
            If prev is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, next_chain
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 8, next_chain
            End If
            Let order_prev be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
            Let order_next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 24
            If order_prev is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 24, order_next
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with order_prev, 24, order_next
            End If
            If order_next is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 32, order_prev
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with order_next, 16, order_prev
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with cur
            Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 16
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with os, 16, count minus 1
            Return 1
        End If
        Set prev to cur
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Size accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read count field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_size" takes os as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
First/last/next entry accessors for iteration.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read header order_head, order_tail; for entry next, read offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_first" takes os as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Last entry (most recently inserted).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read order_tail field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_last" takes os as Integer returns Integer:
    If os is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with os, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Entry's next link in insertion order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read offset 24 of entry.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_entry_next" takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Entry's stored value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read offset 0 of entry.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "oset_entry_value" takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 0
End Process
